    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-07T09:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 7, 1948—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 7—7:13 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>822. For Butterworth from Clark.<note n="12" xml:id="d260fn12">Lewis Clark,
                        Minister-Counselor of Embassy.</note> You will be interested ComNavWesPac
                    despatch 030045, May 2 [<hi rend="italic">3</hi>], to CNO regarding possibility
                    Communist attack on Tsingtao. See also my letter to you April 22.<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d260fn13">Not printed.</note> [Clark.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
